infer \\textit{whether} bipolar\noscillations had occurred within the protoneutron star envelope, and (ii) if\nthe measurements are able to sample the full amplitude of the neutrino\noscillations in vacuum, then the amplitude of the prior bipolar oscillations is\nalso well predicted. This result intimates that the inference paradigm can well\ncomplement numerical integration codes, via its ability to infer flavor\nevolution at physically inaccessible locations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Jan 2022 00:56:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-18"}
